<b>q3</b></td><td><ul><li class="letterDescription">
In earlier lessons, you saw <b>que</b> abbreviated by a <b>q</b> followed by a mark of abbreviation that looks like a colon or semicolon: <b>q:</b> or <b>q;</b> . In this manuscript, that is represented by <b>q</b> followed by what looks like a <b>3</b>. This is actually a variation on <b>q;</b> in which the semicolon-like mark is written with two curved strokes.</li></ul></td></tr>


<tr><td><b>.N.</b></td><td><ul><li class="letterDescription">
