  <tr><td><b>q</b> with strokes through the descender
  
 </td><td><ul><li class="letterDescription">The <b>q</b> with a straight horizontal line through its descender stands for <b>qui</b>. A <b>q</b> with a stroke through its descender that curves diagonally up to the right stands for <b>qua</b>. If you put those abbreviations together with what you know about how the common mark of abbreviation works, you should be able to work out any more complex abbreviations on this page that you have not seen before.</li></ul></td></tr>
